      "content": "it’s just that \"getting better\" feels like a lie people tell to keep you going. like, i'm just exhausted from the cycle of trying and failing and trying again. i feel like i'm just performing a version of myself that everyone expects, but the real me is just... gone. sometimes i look at it all and think, wouldn't it just be easier if i didn't have to wake up and face this version of reality anymore? wouldn't it be better if everything just went quiet?",
